statistics.name: assists
statistics.description: The number of times a player who passes the ball to a teammate in a way that leads to a score by field goal, meaning that he or she was "assisting" in the basket. There is some judgment involved in deciding whether a passer should be credited with an assist.

statistics.name: turnovers
statistics.description: The number of times a player loses possession to the other team.

statistics.name: minutes
statistics.description: The total number of minutes played.

statistics.name: assistTurnoverRatio
statistics.description: The average number of assists a player or team records per turnover

statistics.name: rebounds
statistics.description: The total number of rebounds (offensive and defensive).

article.description: Jer'Vaughn Johnson scored 18 points and Perry Webster had 17 points and eight assists as Cal State Fullerton rolled to a 76-48 victory over Occidental.
article.headline: Cal State Fullerton rolls to win over Occidental
article.linkText: Cal State Fullerton rolls to win over Occidental
article.story: FULLERTON, Calif. -- Jer'Vaughn Johnson scored 18 points and Perry Webster had 17 points and eight assists as Cal State Fullerton rolled to a 76-48 victory over Occidental on Saturday night. Isiah Umipig added a career-high 15 points and Orane Chin had 12 for the Titans (4-7), who shot 59 percent from the field and improved to 3-0 at home this season. Deshun McCoy had 17 points and Kris Montoya 14 for Occidental (4-3), a Division III school that is now 0-7 all-time against Fullerton. The Tigers led 15-10 midway through the first half before Fullerton went on an 8-0 run en route to a 29-24 halftime lead. Occidental was still within 38-33 when the Titans scored 11 straight points to put the game out of reach. Fullerton dominated inside, outscoring the Tigers 32-6 on points in the paint, and scored 22 points off of Occidental's 18 turnovers.
